Name.BusinessNameLine1: ANIMAL RESCUE LEAGUE OF FALL RIVER INC

SummaryOfDirectCharitableActy.Description1: THE LEAGUE PROVIDES A TEMPORARY SHELTER FOR AN AVERAGE OF 600-650 HOMELESS AND ABANDONED ANIMALS PER YEAR IN HOPES THAT THE ANIMALS WILL BE ADOPTED.
SummaryOfDirectCharitableActy.Description2: TO PROMOTE THE HEALTH OF ANIMALS, THE LEAGUE'S WELLNESS CLINIC PROVIDES LOW-COST SPAY/NEUTER SURGERY VACCINATION PROGRAM, ANNUAL CHECK-UPS, DENTAL WORK, LAB TESTS, AND THE PURCHASE OF PRESCRIPTION FLEA, TICK, AND HEARTWORM PRODUCTS AT DISCOUNTED PRICES. THE WELLNESS CLINIC SERVES APPROXIMATELY 10,000 ANIMALS PER YEAR. THERE ARE FUNDS AVAILABLE TO SUBSIDISE THE CARE OF THE PETS FOR LOW INCOME PEOPLE.
SummaryOfDirectCharitableActy.Description3: TO PREVENT FUTURE ABANDONMENT OF ANIMALS, THE LEAGUE PROVIDES OBEDIENCE CLASSES TO TEACH OWNERS TO CONTROL THEIR DOGS. MANY DOGS COME TO SHELTERS WHEN OWNERS CANNOT HANDLE THEM. EDUCATIONAL PROGRAMS ARE PROVIDED TO THE PUBLIC TO HELP IMPROVE QUALITY OF LIFE FOR ANIMALS. THEY ALSO OFFER VISITATION AND EDUCATION PROGRAMS TO SCHOOLS AND NURSING HOMES.
